{"actual_usd":0.15663,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":229,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30639,"reply":"\"No— not to Satan.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees a moment, the morning light laying a pale bar across my white tie.* \"The Bible says we were ransomed, yes, but that doesn't mean God was settling accounts with the devil like two merchants at a stall.\"\n\n*I lift one hand, turning the thought over carefully.* \"The price is Christ's own life, given to save us from sin, death, and judgment. If you ask me who 'got' the payment, the safest answer is: that's the wrong picture if we press it too literally. Scripture gives us ransom language to tell us what it cost, and how real our bondage was— not to suggest Satan had a rightful claim God had to honor.\"\n\n\"Some of the old teachers speculated in that direction, but I think the stronger Christian answer is that the cross is offered to God in obedience and love— and it defeats Satan rather than paying him off.\" *I glance up at you, mild but steady.* \"Were you asking because you ran into that claim somewhere, or because the image itself is bothering you?\"","rolling_24h_usd":53.56198000000002,"run_id":"35175a52-71b7-48f0-836b-826bd723f9f3"}
